description = Retrieve, capture, or refresh distilled agent-runtime knowledge — the execution layer (harness) that runs an agent: the loop driver, tool dispatch, retries and idempotency, durable execution and restart-survival, session and state persistence, sandboxing, runaway-guards and budgets, triggers and scheduling, and sub-agent spawning. Use when building or debugging the runtime that actually executes an agent loop — how it dispatches tools, retries, checkpoints, sandboxes, or stays within budget — or looking up or saving a runtime concept — not when choosing the control-flow pattern the loop follows (that is agent-architectures), nor when managing what occupies the context window (that is context-engineering).
